“We honestly didn’t make this decision lightly - conscious of how financially difficult it will be for those involved - we hoped up to the last moments,” clarified Mayor Uwe Rumberg (Independent).
“But as event organizers we are responsible in the end for the health of thousands of people”.
If tens of thousands of people during the festival had taken to the festival grounds, no minimum distance, hygiene concepts or contact tracing could be maintained as stipulated by current Corona protection ordinances.
Otherwise, the restrictions would have been so extreme that not much of a folk festival would have remained.
