Nürnberg: Police intervene in an unauthorized tuning meetup with 700 vehicles and about 1,100 people.
Hundreds of cars and over 1,000 people showed up to a tuning meetup Saturday night in the parking lot of a furniture store.
The police have announced their intention to more strictly regulate such events.
A large tuning meetup took place in a city south of Nürnberg this Saturday evening (25 July, 2020).
Many hundreds of vehicles took part.
According to Mittelfranken Police, an increase presence of vehicles in the area of a large parking lot near a street in Ingolstadt was determined at 22:30h by Nürnberg Police.
That is why the police then carried out multiple vehicle inspections there.
The police have only recently announced their intention to take stronger action against so-called “car posers”.
